<paragraph id="8BC53698FFB4FFBCEBF31057FDC35259" blockId="52.[158,585,1097,1121]" box="[158,585,1097,1121]" pageId="52" pageNumber="52">
<heading id="D08D81F4FFB4FFBCEBF31057FDC35259" box="[158,585,1097,1121]" centered="true" fontSize="9" level="2" pageId="52" pageNumber="52" reason="2">
Family 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D1BFFB4FFBCEB9D1057FDC35259" authority="Bonaparte, 1845" authorityName="Bonaparte" authorityYear="1845" box="[240,585,1097,1121]" class="Mammalia" family="Erethizontidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="52" pageNumber="52" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Erethizontidae Bonaparte, 1845</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC53698FFB4FFBCEBF11062FEC253D1" blockId="52.[108,636,1148,1513]" pageId="52" pageNumber="52">
The New World porcupines in the family 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D1BFFB4FFBCEB011080FE82528E" authorityName="Bonaparte" authorityYear="1845" box="[108,264,1182,1206]" class="Mammalia" family="Erethizontidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="52" pageNumber="52" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Erethizontidae</taxonomicName>
are medium-to-large sized nocturnal, arboreal, herbivorous rodents that have their bodies covered with spines used for defense (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FFB4FFBCE92110FCFE9A5324" author="Barthelmess, E. L." pageId="52" pageNumber="52" pagination="372 - 397" refId="ref33068" refString="Barthelmess, E. L. 2016. Family Erethizontidae (New World porcupines). In D. E. Wilson, T. E. Lacher, Jr., and R. A. Mittermeier (editors), Handbook of the mammals of the world: 372 - 397. Barcelona: Lynx Edicions." type="book chapter" year="2016">Barthelmess, 2016</bibRefCitation>
). Currently, the family comprises 17 species that are grouped into three genera, two of these monotypic (
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D1BFFB4FFBCEA3A1156FE475358" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1843" box="[343,461,1352,1376]" class="Mammalia" family="Erethizontidae" genus="Chaetomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="52" pageNumber="52" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90EEA8AFFB4FFBCEA3A1156FE475358" box="[343,461,1352,1376]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="52">Chaetomys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D1BFFB4FFBCE9661156FDF95358" authorityName="F. Cuvier" authorityYear="1823" box="[523,627,1352,1376]" class="Mammalia" family="Erethizontidae" genus="Erethizon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="52" pageNumber="52" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90EEA8AFFB4FFBCE9661156FDF95358" box="[523,627,1352,1376]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="52">Erethizon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FFB4FFBCEB191175FF6153BA" author="Voss, R. S." box="[116,235,1386,1411]" pageId="52" pageNumber="52" pagination="786 - 805" refId="ref43780" refString="Voss, R. S. 2015. Superfamily Erethizontoidea Bonaparte, 1845. In J. L. Patton, U. F. J. Pardinas, and G. D'Elia (editors), Mammals of South America, vol. 2: Rodents: 786 - 805. Chicago: University of Chicago Press." type="book chapter" year="2015">Voss, 2015</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FFB4FFBCEB981175FE3653BA" author="Barthelmess, E. L." box="[245,444,1386,1411]" pageId="52" pageNumber="52" pagination="372 - 397" refId="ref33068" refString="Barthelmess, E. L. 2016. Family Erethizontidae (New World porcupines). In D. E. Wilson, T. E. Lacher, Jr., and R. A. Mittermeier (editors), Handbook of the mammals of the world: 372 - 397. Barcelona: Lynx Edicions." type="book chapter" year="2016">Barthelmess, 2016</bibRefCitation>
). The third, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D1BFFB4FFBCE9501175FF1E539D" authorityName="Lacepede" authorityYear="1799" class="Mammalia" family="Erethizontidae" genus="Coendou" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="52" pageNumber="52" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90EEA8AFFB4FFBCE9501175FF1E539D" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="52">Coendou</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, contains most of the diversity and its species are distributed in Central and South America (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FFB4FFBCEB1E11CFFEB753D1" author="Barthelmess, E. L." box="[115,317,1489,1513]" pageId="52" pageNumber="52" pagination="372 - 397" refId="ref33068" refString="Barthelmess, E. L. 2016. Family Erethizontidae (New World porcupines). In D. E. Wilson, T. E. Lacher, Jr., and R. A. Mittermeier (editors), Handbook of the mammals of the world: 372 - 397. Barcelona: Lynx Edicions." type="book chapter" year="2016">Barthelmess, 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
